The discography of [[Eternal (band)|Eternal]], a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[pop music]] group, consists of four [[studio album]]s, five [[compilation album]], one [[remix album]] and nineteen [[single (music)|singles]] on [[EMI|EMI Records]].

In 1993 they released their debut single "Stay", which reached Top 5 in the United Kingdom and Top 20 on the U.S. Billboard Hot 100.   The group's debut album "Always & Forever" was released in November 1993, peaked at #2, and made Eternal the first all-female group to sell over a million copies of an album in the UK, certified 4xPlatinum by March 1995.  Their second album "Power of a Woman" was released in October 1995. The #6 charting album produced four Top 10 singles, including the number seven single "I Am Blessed".  "Before the Rain", their third album, was released in March 1997. It was certified platinum in the UK.  In October of that same year, the group released Greatest Hits.. The album peaked at #2 and produced a further Top 5 single "Angel of Mine".  Eternal released their self-titled fourth album in November 1999, peaking at #87 the album had very little promotion .

